Introduction

Racial discrimination is a universal problem. From the perspective of the world, as long as there are different races, there will be racial discrimination. White, black, yellow, European, American, Asian, there are different degrees of discrimination among each other, some with respect on the outside and contempt on the inside, some with deep hostility. According to the chart below, we find that the largest number of black race people in prison was in 2004, with ( 1.7736^{4}). Even today, the incarceration rate for blacks is about 0.4 percent (0.0049136). However, for whites, the incarceration rate was 0.1 percent (0.0015731). Regionally, the WI is probably the most discriminating state for blacks.Social unrest over racial discrimination has led to frequent protests.Therefore, I hope to use my data and charts on the incarceration rate of black race from 1990 to 2018 to show the unequal treatment of black race based on black race prision admission rate and total black race people population, so that the public can pay more attention to this problem and solve it fundamentally.
